The paper deals with a problem in wireless networks, specifically joint power and admission control, which falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper proposes a non-convex approximation approach for solving the problem, which involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, indicating a focus on theoretical computer science.
